    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required gradation levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 1 against a required Gradation 2; this gap is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 is a single standardized protocol and the COU does not require multi-condition extrapolation. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The assessment team notes strong corroborating evidence from the Rohlmann et al. rigid-block dataset, which showed 3.8% mean stiffness agreement with FEA predictions, further supporting model credibility. Overall credibility is judged sufficient for a Medium model risk, Medium decision consequence COU. Decision: Accepted.",
